{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Hello. Actually, that's \"hello\" in Bauer Bodoni"},{"time":5000,"text":"for the typographically hysterical amongst us."},{"time":8000,"text":"One of the threads that seems to have come through"},{"time":11000,"text":"loud and clear in the last couple of days"},{"time":14000,"text":"is this need to reconcile what the Big wants --"},{"time":18000,"text":"the \"Big\" being the organization, the system, the country --"},{"time":24000,"text":"and what the \"Small\" wants -- the individual, the person."},{"time":27000,"text":"And how do you bring those two things together?"},{"time":29000,"text":"Charlie Ledbetter, yesterday, I thought, talked very articulately"},{"time":31000,"text":"about this need to bring consumers, to bring people"},{"time":35000,"text":"into the process of creating things."},{"time":37000,"text":"And that's what I want to talk about today."},{"time":40000,"text":"So, bringing together the Small to help facilitate and create the Big,"},{"time":46000,"text":"I think, is something that we believe in -- something I believe in,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and something that we kind of bring to life"},{"time":51000,"text":"through what we do at Ideo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"I call this first chapter -- for the Brits in the room --"},{"time":56000,"text":"the \"Blinding Glimpse of the Bleeding Obvious.\""},{"time":58000,"text":"Often, the good ideas are so staring-at-you-right-in-the-face"},{"time":62000,"text":"that you kind of miss them. And I think, a lot of times,"},{"time":65000,"text":"what we do is just, sort of, hold the mirror up to our clients, and sort of go,"},{"time":68000,"text":"\"Duh! You know, look what's really going on.\""},{"time":71000,"text":"And rather than talk about it in the theory,"},{"time":73000,"text":"I think I'm just going to show you an example."},{"time":75000,"text":"We were asked by a large healthcare system in Minnesota"},{"time":80000,"text":"to describe to them what their patient experience was."},{"time":83000,"text":"And I think they were expecting --"},{"time":85000,"text":"they'd worked with lots of consultants before --"},{"time":86000,"text":"I think they were expecting some kind of hideous org chart"},{"time":89000,"text":"with thousands of bubbles and systemic this, that and the other,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and all kinds of mappy stuff."},{"time":95000,"text":"Or even worse, some kind of ghastly death-by-Powerpoint thing"},{"time":99000,"text":"with WowCharts and all kinds of, you know, God knows, whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"The first thing we actually shared with them was this."},{"time":109000,"text":"I'll play this until your eyeballs completely dissolve."},{"time":113000,"text":"This is 59 seconds into the film."},{"time":119000,"text":"This is a minute 59."},{"time":124000,"text":"3:19."},{"time":125000,"text":"I think something happens. I think a head may appear in a second."},{"time":129000,"text":"5:10."},{"time":131000,"text":"5:58."},{"time":133000,"text":"6:20."},{"time":135000,"text":"We showed them the whole cut,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and they were all completely, what is this?"},{"time":139000,"text":"And the point is when you lie in a hospital bed all day,"},{"time":150000,"text":"all you do is look at the roof, and it's a really shitty experience."},{"time":154000,"text":"And just putting yourself in the position of the patient --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"this is Christian, who works with us at Ideo."},{"time":160000,"text":"He just lay in the hospital bed,"},{"time":161000,"text":"and, kind of, stared at the polystyrene ceiling tiles"},{"time":164000,"text":"for a really long time."},{"time":165000,"text":"That's what it's like to be a patient in the hospital."},{"time":168000,"text":"And they were sort, you know, blinding glimpse of bleeding obvious."},{"time":171000,"text":"Oh, my goodness. So, looking at the situation"},{"time":174000,"text":"from the point of view of the person out --"},{"time":177000,"text":"as opposed to the traditional position of the organization in --"},{"time":181000,"text":"was, for these guys, quite a revelation."},{"time":184000,"text":"And so, that was a really catalytic thing for them."},{"time":188000,"text":"So they snapped into action."},{"time":189000,"text":"They said, OK, it's not about systemic change."},{"time":192000,"text":"It's not about huge, ridiculous things that we need to do."},{"time":194000,"text":"It's about tiny things that can make a huge amount of difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"So we started with them prototyping some really little things"},{"time":201000,"text":"that we could do to have a huge amount of impact."},{"time":203000,"text":"The first thing we did was we took a little bicycle mirror"},{"time":207000,"text":"and we Band-Aided it here, onto a gurney, a hospital trolley,"},{"time":212000,"text":"so that when you were wheeled around by a nurse or by a doctor,"},{"time":216000,"text":"you could actually have a conversation with them."},{"time":217000,"text":"You could, kind of, see them in your rear-view mirror,"},{"time":219000,"text":"so it created a tiny human interaction."},{"time":222000,"text":"Very small example of something that they could do."},{"time":225000,"text":"Interestingly, the nurses themselves, sort of, snapped into action --"},{"time":228000,"text":"said, OK, we embrace this. What can we do?"},{"time":231000,"text":"The first thing they do is they decorated the ceiling."},{"time":234000,"text":"Which I thought was really -- I showed this to my mother recently."},{"time":236000,"text":"I think my mother now thinks that I'm some sort of interior decorator."},{"time":239000,"text":"It's what I do for a living, sort of Laurence Llewelyn-Bowen."},{"time":242000,"text":"Not particularly the world's best design solution"},{"time":244000,"text":"for those of us who are real, sort of, hard-core designers,"},{"time":246000,"text":"but nonetheless, a fabulous empathic solution for people."},{"time":252000,"text":"Things that they started doing themselves --"},{"time":254000,"text":"like changing the floor going into the patient's room"},{"time":257000,"text":"so that it signified, \"This is my room. This is my personal space\" --"},{"time":262000,"text":"was a really interesting sort of design solution to the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264000,"text":"So you went from public space to private space."},{"time":266000,"text":"And another idea, again, that came from one of the nurses -- which I love --"},{"time":269000,"text":"was they took traditional, sort of, corporate white boards,"},{"time":273000,"text":"then they put them on one wall of the patient's room,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and they put this sticker there."},{"time":277000,"text":"So that what you could actually do was go into the room"},{"time":280000,"text":"and write messages to the person who was sick in that room,"},{"time":283000,"text":"which was lovely."},{"time":284000,"text":"So, tiny, tiny, tiny solutions that made a huge amount of impact."},{"time":289000,"text":"I thought that was a really, really nice example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"So this is not particularly a new idea,"},{"time":295000,"text":"kind of, seeing opportunities in things that are around you"},{"time":299000,"text":"and snapping and turning them into a solution."},{"time":301000,"text":"It's a history of invention based around this."},{"time":304000,"text":"I'm going to read this because I want to get these names right."},{"time":306000,"text":"Joan Ganz Cooney saw her daughter -- came down on a Saturday morning,"},{"time":310000,"text":"saw her daughter watching the test card,"},{"time":312000,"text":"waiting for programs to come on one morning"},{"time":315000,"text":"and from that came Sesame Street."},{"time":319000,"text":"Malcolm McLean was moving from one country to another"},{"time":323000,"text":"and was wondering why it took these guys so long"},{"time":325000,"text":"to get the boxes onto the ship."},{"time":328000,"text":"And he invented the shipping container."},{"time":331000,"text":"George de Mestral -- this is not bugs all over a Birkenstock --"},{"time":335000,"text":"was walking his dog in a field and got covered in burrs,"},{"time":338000,"text":"sort of little prickly things, and from that came Velcro."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"And finally, for the Brits, Percy Shaw -- this is a big British invention --"},{"time":350000,"text":"saw the cat's eyes at the side of the road,"},{"time":351000,"text":"when he was driving home one night and from that came the Catseye."},{"time":356000,"text":"So there's a whole series of just using your eyes,"},{"time":358000,"text":"seeing things for the first time, seeing things afresh"},{"time":361000,"text":"and using them as an opportunity to create new possibilities."},{"time":365000,"text":"Second one, without sounding overly Zen,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and this is a quote from the Buddha:"},{"time":369000,"text":"\"Finding yourself in the margins, looking to the edges of things,"},{"time":373000,"text":"is often a really interesting place to start.\""},{"time":376000,"text":"Blinkered vision tends to produce, I think, blinkered solutions."},{"time":380000,"text":"So, looking wide, using your peripheral vision,"},{"time":383000,"text":"is a really interesting place to look for opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"Again, another medical example here."},{"time":389000,"text":"We were asked by a device producer --"},{"time":392000,"text":"we did the Palm Pilot and the Treo."},{"time":394000,"text":"We did a lot of sexy tech at Ideo --"},{"time":396000,"text":"they'd seen this and they wanted a sexy piece of technology"},{"time":399000,"text":"for medical diagnostics."},{"time":401000,"text":"This was a device that a nurse uses"},{"time":403000,"text":"when they're doing a spinal procedure in hospital."},{"time":405000,"text":"They'll ask the nurses to input data."},{"time":407000,"text":"And they had this vision of the nurse, kind of, clicking away"},{"time":409000,"text":"on this aluminum device"},{"time":410000,"text":"and it all being incredibly, sort of, gadget-lustish."},{"time":415000,"text":"When we actually went and watched this procedure taking place --"},{"time":419000,"text":"and I'll explain this in a second --"},{"time":421000,"text":"it became very obvious that there was a human dimension to this"},{"time":425000,"text":"that they really weren't recognizing."},{"time":428000,"text":"When you're having a four-inch needle inserted into your spine --"},{"time":432000,"text":"which was the procedure that this device's data was about;"},{"time":436000,"text":"it was for pain management -- you're shit scared; you're freaking out."},{"time":440000,"text":"And so the first thing that pretty much every nurse did,"},{"time":444000,"text":"was hold the patient's hand to comfort them. Human gesture --"},{"time":448000,"text":"which made the fabulous two-handed data input completely impossible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"So, the thing that we designed, much less sexy"},{"time":458000,"text":"but much more human and practical, was this."},{"time":463000,"text":"So, it's not a Palm Pilot by any stretch of the imagination,"},{"time":465000,"text":"but it has a thumb-scroll so you can do everything with one hand."},{"time":468000,"text":"So, again, going back to this -- the idea that a tiny human gesture"},{"time":474000,"text":"dictated the design of this product."},{"time":477000,"text":"And I think that's really, really important."},{"time":480000,"text":"So, again, this idea of workarounds."},{"time":482000,"text":"We use this phrase \"workarounds\" a lot,"},{"time":484000,"text":"sort of, looking around us. I was actually looking around the TED"},{"time":486000,"text":"and just watching all of these kind of things happen"},{"time":488000,"text":"while I've been here."},{"time":489000,"text":"This idea of the way that people cobble together solutions in our life --"},{"time":493000,"text":"and the things we kind of do in our environment"},{"time":496000,"text":"that are somewhat subconscious but have huge potential --"},{"time":498000,"text":"is something that we look at a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"We wrote a book recently, I think you might have received it,"},{"time":503000,"text":"called \"Thoughtless Acts?\""},{"time":504000,"text":"It's been all about these kind of thoughtless things that people do,"},{"time":507000,"text":"which have huge intention and huge opportunity."},{"time":510000,"text":"Why do we all follow the line in the street?"},{"time":513000,"text":"This is a picture in a Japanese subway."},{"time":515000,"text":"People consciously follow things even though, why, we don't know."},{"time":521000,"text":"Why do we line up the square milk carton with the square fence?"},{"time":525000,"text":"Because we kind of have to -- we're just compelled to."},{"time":529000,"text":"We don't know why, but we do."},{"time":533000,"text":"Why do we wrap the teabag string around the cup handle?"},{"time":536000,"text":"Again, we're sort of using the world around us"},{"time":539000,"text":"to create our own design solutions."},{"time":541000,"text":"And we're always saying to our clients: \"You should look at this stuff."},{"time":544000,"text":"This stuff is really important. This stuff is really vital.\""},{"time":546000,"text":"This is people designing their own experiences."},{"time":548000,"text":"You can draw from this."},{"time":552000,"text":"We sort of assume that because there's a pole in the street,"},{"time":554000,"text":"that it's okay to use it, so we park our shopping cart there."},{"time":559000,"text":"It's there for our use, on some level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"So, again, we sort of co-opt our environment"},{"time":563000,"text":"to do all these different things."},{"time":566000,"text":"We co-opt other experiences --"},{"time":567000,"text":"we take one item and transfer it to another."},{"time":571000,"text":"And this is my favorite one. My mother used to say to me,"},{"time":573000,"text":"\"Just because your sister jumps in the lake doesn't mean you have to.\""},{"time":576000,"text":"But, of course, we all do. We all follow each other every day."},{"time":578000,"text":"So somebody assumes"},{"time":579000,"text":"that because somebody else has done something,"},{"time":581000,"text":"that's permission for them to do the same thing."},{"time":584000,"text":"And there's almost this sort of semaphore around us all the time."},{"time":587000,"text":"I mean, shopping bag equals \"parking meter out of order.\""},{"time":590000,"text":"And we all, kind of, know how to read these signals now."},{"time":592000,"text":"We all talk to one another in this highly visual way"},{"time":595000,"text":"without realizing what we're doing."},{"time":598000,"text":"Third section is this idea of not knowing,"},{"time":602000,"text":"of consciously putting yourself backwards."},{"time":604000,"text":"I talk about unthinking situations all the time."},{"time":607000,"text":"Sort of having beginner's mind, scraping your mind clean"},{"time":609000,"text":"and looking at things afresh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"A friend of mine was a designer at IKEA,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and he was asked by his boss"},{"time":616000,"text":"to help design a storage system for children."},{"time":619000,"text":"This is the Billy bookcase -- it's IKEA's biggest selling product."},{"time":622000,"text":"Hammer it together. Hammer it together with a shoe, if you're me,"},{"time":624000,"text":"because they're impossible to assemble."},{"time":626000,"text":"But big selling bookcase. How do we replicate this for children?"},{"time":632000,"text":"The reality is when you actually watch children,"},{"time":635000,"text":"children don't think about things like storage in linear terms."},{"time":638000,"text":"Children assume permission in a very different way."},{"time":641000,"text":"Children live on things. They live under things."},{"time":643000,"text":"They live around things,"},{"time":645000,"text":"and so their spatial awareness relationship,"},{"time":648000,"text":"and their thinking around storage is totally different."},{"time":650000,"text":"So the first thing you have to do -- this is Graham, the designer --"},{"time":653000,"text":"is, sort of, put yourself in their shoes. And so, here he is"},{"time":656000,"text":"sitting under the table."},{"time":658000,"text":"So, what came out of this?"},{"time":660000,"text":"This is the storage system that he designed."},{"time":663000,"text":"So what is this? I hear you all ask. No, I don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":668000,"text":"It's this, and I think this is a particularly lovely solution."},{"time":672000,"text":"So, you know, it's a totally different way of looking at the situation."},{"time":675000,"text":"It's a completely empathic solution --"},{"time":679000,"text":"apart from the fact that teddy's probably not loving it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"But a really nice way of re-framing the ordinary,"},{"time":690000,"text":"and I think that's one of the things."},{"time":691000,"text":"And putting yourself in the position of the person,"},{"time":694000,"text":"and I think that's one of the threads that I've heard again"},{"time":696000,"text":"from this conference is how do we put ourselves"},{"time":698000,"text":"in other peoples' shoes and really feel what they feel?"},{"time":700000,"text":"And then use that information to fuel solutions?"},{"time":703000,"text":"And I think that's what this is very much about."},{"time":707000,"text":"Last section: green armband. We've all got them."},{"time":711000,"text":"It's about this really."},{"time":713000,"text":"I mean, it's about picking battles big enough to matter"},{"time":715000,"text":"but small enough to win."},{"time":717000,"text":"Again, that's one of the themes"},{"time":718000,"text":"that I think has come through loud and clear in this conference"},{"time":721000,"text":"is: Where do we start? How do we start? What do we do to start?"},{"time":725000,"text":"So, again, we were asked to design a water pump"},{"time":729000,"text":"for a company called ApproTEC, in Kenya."},{"time":731000,"text":"They're now called KickStart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"And, again, as designers,"},{"time":735000,"text":"we wanted to make this thing incredibly beautiful"},{"time":737000,"text":"and spend a lot of time thinking of the form."},{"time":740000,"text":"And that was completely irrelevant."},{"time":741000,"text":"When you put yourself in the position of these people,"},{"time":746000,"text":"things like the fact that this has to be able to fold up"},{"time":748000,"text":"and fit on a bicycle, become much more relevant"},{"time":751000,"text":"than the form of it. The way it's produced,"},{"time":753000,"text":"it has to be produced with indigenous manufacturing methods"},{"time":756000,"text":"and indigenous materials."},{"time":758000,"text":"So it had to be looked at completely from the point of view of the user."},{"time":762000,"text":"We had to completely transfer ourselves over to their world."},{"time":766000,"text":"So what seems like a very clunky product"},{"time":768000,"text":"is, in fact, incredibly useful."},{"time":771000,"text":"It's powered a bit like a Stairmaster -- you pump up and down on it."},{"time":774000,"text":"Children can use it. Adults can use it. Everybody uses it."},{"time":777000,"text":"It's turning these guys -- again, one of the themes --"},{"time":780000,"text":"it's turning them into entrepreneurs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"These guys are using this very successfully."},{"time":785000,"text":"And for us, it's been great"},{"time":786000,"text":"because it's won loads of design awards."},{"time":787000,"text":"So we actually managed to reconcile the needs of the design company,"},{"time":790000,"text":"the needs of the individuals in the company,"},{"time":792000,"text":"to feel good about a product we were actually designing,"},{"time":794000,"text":"and the needs of the individuals we were designing it for."},{"time":799000,"text":"There it is, pumping water from 30 feet."},{"time":803000,"text":"So as a final gesture we handed out these bracelets"},{"time":808000,"text":"to all of you this morning."},{"time":809000,"text":"We've made a donation on everybody's behalf here"},{"time":812000,"text":"to kick start, no pun intended, their next project."},{"time":816000,"text":"Because, again, I think, sort of, putting our money where our mouth is, here."},{"time":820000,"text":"We feel that this is an important gesture."},{"time":822000,"text":"So we've handed out bracelets. Small is the new big."},{"time":824000,"text":"I hope you'll all wear them."},{"time":825000,"text":"So that's it. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}